As used in this section:
"Alternative fuel facility" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010;
"Approved company" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010;
"Authority" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010;
"Base amount" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010;
"Capital investment" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010;
"Eligible project" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010;
"Energy-efficient alternative fuel facility" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010;
"Gasification facility" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010; and
"Tax incentive agreement" has the same meaning as in KRS 154.27-010.

A company approved for incentives under KRS 154.27-060 shall file a request for the incentive with the department within sixty (60) days of the completion of the construction, retrofit, or upgrade of the facility. In subsequent years, the approved company shall file a request for the incentive within sixty (60) days following the end of each calendar year. The request for incentives shall be in the form prescribed by the department through the promulgation of administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A. The request for incentives shall include but not be limited to the following information:
Verification of the base amount;
Verification of the tons of coal purchased and used or severed and used by the approved company as feedstock for an alternative fuel facility, energy-efficient alternative fuel facility, or gasification facility during the calendar year for which the request for incentives is being made;
Verification that the minimum capital investment as set forth in the tax incentive agreement has been made;
Verification of the output of coal-derived alternative transportation fuels, coal-derived synthetic natural gas, coal-derived liquid fuels, coal-derived energy-efficient alternative fuels, or other coal-derived chemicals or chemical feedstocks; and
Any other information that the department may require.

To assist in determining the amount of coal purchased and used or severed and used that is eligible for the incentive, the department shall obtain from the University of Kentucky Center for Applied Energy Research a reasonable and typical estimate of the tons of coal needed to produce a given output of coal-derived alternative transportation fuels, coal-derived synthetic natural gas, coal-derived liquid fuels, coal-derived energy-efficient alternative fuels, or other coal-derived chemicals or chemical feedstocks, considering:
The type of coal to be used;
Equipment to be employed;
Size and output of the facility;
Slate of products produced; and
Other characteristics of the alternative fuel facility, energy-efficient alternative fuel facility, or gasification facility.
